# ============================================================
# SECTION X - GENERAL-AGENT routing discharge (M3.12 reframe)
#
# Operator pushback 2026-05-03: "if we do alot of research and minimal
# experimentation on when 'top general models' of different price points
# 'fail' on speed or intelligence we can help suggest an update to our
# burhan plan that gives us more value to our cheapcode fork and help us
# reach our most valuable version of our product 'general agent'."
#
# This section adds the load-bearing routing-decision claims that
# operationalize cheapcode's value as a general-agent router. Each rule
# pairs a task-shape with the documented value-optimum model. Falsifiers
# are independent re-evals showing the published per-model envelope is
# wrong.
#
# Compositional with sections G/V/W: cheapcode_v1_ships still requires
# the phase plan; this section adds a NEW discharge for the general-agent
# value claim that cheapcode v1.0 carries forward (or scopes for v1.x).
