# ============================================================
# SECTION Y - substrate-runtime cross-witness voter (M3.18 → M3.20)
#
# Operationalizes Khazīna atom 0016's runtime interpretation on the
# benchmark fit M3.2 retrospective said was missing: hard-reasoning
# (AIME / olympiad / multi-step proofs). Failure mode = chain-of-
# reasoning consistency, which is substrate's strength (atom 0010
# cross-witness, atom 0015 transfer-overstated).
#
# Pipeline: parallel cheap × 2 → if converge return sahih → else
# escalate to smart → if 2-of-3 majority return hasan → else daif.
#
# Cost projection: ~$0.001-0.020/task (vs M3.10 compound $0.05-0.46).
# Latency projection: ~3-15s P50 (vs M3.10 compound 30-90s).
# Smart-axis: probabilistic per convergence rate; tested by M3.19 probe.
#
# Confidence (pre-M3.19): @>=0.55 — research-grounded plus structural fit.
# Confidence (post-M3.19, M3.20 update): lifted per per-claim outcome.
# See runs/experiment-2-voter-probe/verdict.md for paired evidence.
#
# M3.19 outcome (N=5 mixed benchmark, 3 hard AIME + 2 known-impossible):
#   - Total: 4/5 correct, $0.0516, P50 60s
#   - Sahih convergence precision: 2/2 = 100% (negation-only subset)
#   - Hasan (escalated majority correct): 2/3 = 67%
#   - Negation-asymmetry hypothesis (atom 0010): strongly supported.
#     Negation tasks: 100% sahih, mean 17s, $0.0002/task.
#     Positive tasks: 0% sahih, 100% escalation, mean 158s, $0.017/task.
# ============================================================

# Routing rule 11 observation — voter dispatched without hangs on 5/5
# tasks vs M3.13's 50-min hang on AIME-I-11. M3.20 lift: 0.55 → 0.75.
