# ============================================================
# SECTION Z - voter-vs-direct-frontier paired evidence (M3.23 QW1.1)
#
# M3.23 QW1.1 ran the M3.19 positive AIME tasks (N=3) against direct
# openai/gpt-5 dispatch for paired comparison. Closes the missing piece
# that M3.19 alone couldn't: "is the voter actually doing useful work
# vs just calling the strongest frontier directly?"
#
# Result: voter beats direct gpt-5 on 2 of 3 axes at N=3.
#   - cost:       voter $0.0512 / gpt-5 $0.0658 = 0.78× ✓ voter cheaper
#   - completion: voter 2/3 / gpt-5 1/3 = +1 ✓ voter higher
#   - latency:    voter 184s / gpt-5 131s = 1.40× ✗ voter slower
#
# AIME-I-11 was structural-failure for both pipelines (gpt-5 hit 5min
# timeout; voter produced daif at 230s). AIME-I-14 was the cleanest
# discriminator: gpt-5 confidently wrong (answered 6, gold 104), voter
# escalated and converged correctly. AIME-II-13: both correct, voter at
# half the cost.
#
# Confidence: lifting voter-cost claim toward sahih-band (well-supported)
# and adding new claim for completion-lift. Latency claim STAYS falsified
# at strict ratio.
# ============================================================

