# ============================================================
# SECTION AA - M17/atom-0017 cycle outputs (M3.24)
#
# The mizaj-17 / khazina-0017 cycle was applied to the M3.19 results.jsonl
# byproducts (per-witness answers, not just headline convergence). The
# inventory revealed that AIME-I-11's "daif=null" outcome was hiding the
# fact that cheap-b had returned the gold answer "371" — but cheap-a
# abstained (extraction failed) and smart-c hit timeout, so the voter's
# 2-of-3-majority rule rejected the lone correct answer and returned
# agreed_answer=null.
#
# This is the byproduct that the headline metric ("4/5 correct") averaged
# over. Lifted to falsifier-bearing claim per mizaj 01:
#   - hypothesis: when exactly one witness extracts an answer and the others
#     abstain (null), preserving that single-witness answer with daif grade
#     yields strictly higher information content than null-with-daif.
#   - falsifier: paired test on N≥3 single-witness cases shows the rescued
#     answer is wrong in ≥2 of 3, AND no caller-side use of the daif grade
#     can compensate. Then atom 0015 fires.
#
# Cost: $0 marginal (replays existing M3.19 data with new aggregation rule).
# Implementation: src/cross-witness-voter.ts step 5a (10 LoC). Tests: 2 new
# in cross-witness-voter.test.ts (rescue + counter-test). 34 pass / 0 fail.
# ============================================================

# Empirical claim — single-witness rescue improves completion at zero cost
# on the M3.19 N=5 mixed benchmark (5/5 correct vs 4/5 pre-fix).
# Confidence modest because (a) N=1 case where it fired (b) generality
# untested on broader data — atom 0011 + atom 0015 caveats apply.
# M3.35 cycle 4 inventory (atom 0017 byproduct cycle on M3.27 v0 cached
# data): re-checked the 3 v0 artifacts. ZERO additional firings — Q1/Q2
# had all 3 witnesses produce answers (no abstain); Q3 had 2-of-3 produce
# answers with disagreement (a 2-witness-disagreement case, not a
# 1-witness-rescue case). Net N still 1. This is a STRUCTURAL finding
# about the rescue rule's applicability: it fires when 2-of-3 witnesses
# ABSTAIN (extraction failure), not on 2-of-3 disagreement. The rule
# is well-targeted to AIME-style integer-extract tasks where extract
# failure is the dominant residue mode. NO confidence lift; atom 0011
# honest about persistent small N.
claim obs_single_witness_rescue_introduces_more_wrong_than_right_falsified: Bool @>=0.99 = False
claim single_witness_rescue_strictly_improves_information_content: Bool @>=0.55 = not obs_single_witness_rescue_introduces_more_wrong_than_right_falsified
falsified_when obs_single_witness_rescue_introduces_more_wrong_than_right_falsified

# Process claim — applying the M17 cycle on existing residue produced a
# leveraged improvement at $0 marginal cost. M3.24 cycle B re-aggregated
# M3.19 results.jsonl and confirmed AIME-I-11 → correct (gold "371"), so
# completion 4/5 → 5/5 with the new rule applied. This is the empirical
# anchor for atom 0017 (unknowns-as-positive-data-recursion) within cheapcode.
# M3.25 update: confidence 0.78 → 0.85 — empirically validated by data
# recompute (cycle B), not just logical deduction.
