# M3.30 CORRECTION (atom 0015 fired on M3.29 framing):
# M3.29 framed cheapcode as "no agent harness, must build from scratch."
# Operator corrected: cheapcode IS a fork of opencode that improves it.
# The agent harness is INHERITED from upstream opencode (pinned v1.14.33).
# The substrate (mizaj/burhan/atoms/daftar) is the enhancement layer.
# Per operator's 5 axes, cheapcode improves opencode by:
#   1. Enhancing context (atom 0010 cross-witness pulls independent
#      witness training data)
#   2. Solidifying ethics (mizaj 01 falsifier-first, mizaj 14 sahih/hasan/
#      daif grading prevents agent drift)
#   3. Increasing knowledgeability (v1x panel-of-experts adds family
#      diversity beyond single-model dispatch)
#   4. Improving innovation (atom 0017 byproduct-recursion surfaces gaps
#      the agent's standard methods miss)
#   5. Reducing hallucinations (atom 0015 transfer-overstated checks +
#      mizaj 14 grading bound confidence to source-tier ceilings)
# These 5 axes are substrate-prescribed enhancements ALREADY VALIDATED
# across M3.x project work (M3.18 voter, M3.20 negation-asymmetry, M3.25
# cycle outputs, M3.28 v1x panel-of-experts beating single-pass Claude).
#
# Honest gap analysis (CORRECTED):
# - Agent harness: INHERITED from opencode via fork. Not a from-scratch
#   build. M3.15 opencode CLI dispatch ProviderInitError is the specific
#   integration bug blocking benchmark runs through cheapcode-tier dispatch.
# - DeepSeek V4 Pro single-pass scores SWE-bench Verified 80.6% per
#   facts/08. With cheapcode's substrate enhancements applied AT THE
#   AGENT-LOOP DECISION POINTS within opencode, the 1.4pp gap to codex's
#   82% is plausibly closeable.
# - What's needed: (a) close M3.15 opencode-CLI dispatch, (b) wire
#   cheapcode-witness v1x into the auto-tier dispatch for hard sub-tasks
#   (planning, code-diagnosis, test-failure analysis), (c) ensure cheap-
#   tier routes routine sub-tasks (file reads, simple edits). Each is
