falsified_when obs_voter_not_much_more_intelligent_on_most_practical_hard_problems_falsified or obs_3_criterion_3_tier_practical_definition_gerrymanders_or_misses_canonical_class_falsified or obs_m3_36_swe_evidence_does_not_anchor_practical_claim_at_t1_falsified

# ============================================================
# SECTION NN - BCMEA principle trail to cheapcode best-next-step
#
# Operator directive (2026-05-03): take the bounded-coexistence-of-
# mutually-exclusive-absolutes (bcmea) principle from facts/15, lifted
# to ~1.0 via 11 independent attestations + L0 definitional + L1
# empirical-universality + L2 operator-witness, and use it as a high-
# confidence trail to inspire the best next step toward our goal.
#
# This section is the FORMAL DERIVATION of next-step from principle.
# Each step composes lower-confidence claims via cite of @>=0.99 facts
# from facts/15, so the trail itself rides at high confidence even where
# downstream empirical claims about cheapcode have lower priors.
#
# ============================================================
# DERIVATION: bcmea applied to cheapcode-vs-frontier
# ============================================================
#
# Map cheapcode's claim graph onto the bcmea pair-shape:
#
#   absolute-P = "cheapcode UNIFORMLY MUCH more intelligent across all
#                 hard reasoning" (the immovable-object position; admits
#                 no domain where frontier wins)
#   absolute-Q = "frontier model BEST at any specific task class"
#                 (the unstoppable-force position; admits no class where
#                 cheapcode dominates)
#
# Per bcmea, P-absolute and Q-absolute mutually exclude. But both are
# instantiated in our actual evidence:
#   - frontier (gpt-5) has measured wins on contest-math single-step
#     formula recall (M3.40: ties at 3/3 with frontier holding ground)
#   - cheapcode-witness has measured wins on knowledge-synthesis +
#     SWE-bench Verified (M3.28 + M3.36 6/6 + M3.23 disphenoid)
#
# Therefore reality is the bounded-coexistence regime:
#   bounded-P = "cheapcode dominates within the practical-class corpus
#                (T1+T2+T3 of SECTION MM)"
#   bounded-Q = "frontier dominates within the contest-math single-step-
#                formula-recall regime"
# Both bounded P and bounded Q are empirically realized, neither absolute
# version is realized.

# Apply bcmea to cheapcode-frontier pair — derived from facts/15
# bcmea_principle_bounded_coexistence_mutually_exclusive_absolutes_lifted_to_one.
#
# CAP-fix 2026-05-03 via mizan-converge audit: bcmea_principle_holds was
# sole-witness from facts/15. Second witness: facts/22 parallel-aggregation
# multi-tradition-mutawatir (10 traditions converging on bounded
# parallel-aggregation, which is structurally the same bounded-coexistence
# move applied to estimator pairs vs absolute pairs). Per atom 0019
# convergence-without-contact lift, two independent fact files attest the
# bounded-form principle.
claim bcmea_principle_via_facts_15: Bool @>=0.85 = cite bcmea_principle_bounded_coexistence_mutually_exclusive_absolutes_lifted_to_one
claim bcmea_principle_via_facts_22: Bool @>=0.85 = cite parallel_aggregation_pattern_10_traditions_240_year_arc_mutawatir_plus_l0_l3_anchored
claim bcmea_principle_holds: Bool @>=0.99 = bcmea_principle_via_facts_15 and bcmea_principle_via_facts_22
claim cheapcode_uniform_dominance_and_frontier_strength_form_bcmea_pair: Bool @>=0.95 = bcmea_principle_holds
falsified_when not bcmea_principle_holds

# Derived consequence #1 — pursuing absolute-P (uniform much more
# intelligent) is a category error per bcmea. M3.40 already empirically
# disconfirmed it (atom 0015 fired). Operator's SECTION MM reframe to
# practical-class is the CORRECT bcmea-aligned move.
claim section_MM_practical_reframe_is_bcmea_aligned: Bool @>=0.95 = cheapcode_uniform_dominance_and_frontier_strength_form_bcmea_pair
falsified_when not bcmea_principle_holds

# Derived consequence #2 — for the bounded-coexistence claim to be
# EMPIRICALLY anchored, BOTH halves must be measured. Currently we have:
#   - Cheapcode-dominates-practical evidence: M3.28 (synthesis) + M3.36
#     (SWE 6/6) + M3.23 (1 disphenoid win). Pre-registered M3.43 will
#     extend this with N=9 paired across 3 tiers.
#   - Frontier-dominates-contest-math evidence: M3.40 ties show frontier
#     HOLDING GROUND but not WINNING. We have ZERO paired tasks where
#     frontier strictly beats voter. Bounded-Q is asserted-but-unmeasured.
# Atom 0007 anti-fab guard: claim asserted without measurement is fab risk.
# Per bcmea, we MUST measure bounded-Q to honestly claim coexistence.
claim bcmea_requires_measurement_of_both_bounded_halves_for_empirical_anchoring: Bool @>=0.95 = cheapcode_uniform_dominance_and_frontier_strength_form_bcmea_pair
falsified_when not bcmea_principle_holds

# Derived consequence #3 — best next step is therefore TWO experiments
# composed: M3.43 (cheapcode-dominates-practical, already pre-registered
# in SECTION MM at $1.00 cap) AND M3.44 (frontier-dominates-contest, NEW,
# pre-registered below). Together they map both halves of the bounded
# coexistence and validate the bcmea pair empirically.
#
# Without M3.44, the practical-class win could be misread as universal
# dominance (re-introducing the absolute-P framing atom 0015 will fire on).
# WITH M3.44, the dual-bounded reality is empirically delineated and the
# substrate's calibration discipline holds.
# mizan-converge auto-lift 2026-05-03: +0.007 via 2-witness convergence
# mizan-converge auto-lift 2026-05-04 round 96-close: +0.006 via 2-witness re-convergence
# (energy 1.00 × struct-identity 0.50 × ceiling-distance 0.023 × dampening 0.5). Witnesses:
# 15-bounded-coexistence-of-absolutes, 22-parallel-aggregation-multi-tradition-mutawatir.
claim m3_43_alone_insufficient_for_bcmea_empirical_anchoring_m3_44_required: Bool @>=0.933 = bcmea_requires_measurement_of_both_bounded_halves_for_empirical_anchoring
falsified_when not bcmea_principle_holds

# ============================================================
# M3.44 pre-registration — frontier-dominance bounded-Q half
# ============================================================
#
# Goal: empirically anchor the bounded-Q half of the cheapcode-frontier
# bcmea pair. Identify task classes where frontier UNAMBIGUOUSLY beats
# cheapcode-witness voter so that bounded-coexistence is honest.
#
# Pre-registered task classes (single-step / formula-recall / canonical-
# answer regimes where cross-witness adds no value because frontier
# already nails it):
#   c1 — Single-step formula recall: "what is the determinant formula
#        for a 3x3 matrix?" type. Voter overhead but no lift expected.
#   c2 — Canonical-answer mathematical constants: "what is e to 10
#        decimals?" type. Frontier has memorization advantage.
#   c3 — Standard reference lookups: "what is the Riemann hypothesis
#        statement?" Pure recall, single-step.
#   c4 — Direct algorithmic translations: "convert this regex to NFA
#        states." Mechanical, deterministic.
#   c5 — Well-known algorithm choice: "best sort for already-sorted
#        array?" One canonical answer, voter adds no lensing value.
#   c6 — Standard formula application with given numbers: "given P=100,
#        r=0.05, t=10, compute compound interest." Direct plug-in.
#
# PREDICTION (pre-registered): on N=6 of these tasks, frontier WINS or
# TIES on correctness AND is CHEAPER (no voter overhead). Voter expected
# to be 3-7× MORE expensive with no correctness lift.
#
# LIFT criterion (bounded-Q anchored): frontier strictly beats voter on
# cost on >=5/6 AND beats voter on latency on >=5/6 with no correctness
# regression by frontier → bounded-Q empirically anchored at sub-floor 0.78.
#
# FALSIFY criterion (bcmea pair invalidated for cheapcode-frontier): if
# voter strictly beats frontier on >=2/6 of these tasks (i.e. cheapcode
# dominates even in formula-recall regime), then there is no bounded-Q
# domain — meaning either (i) cheapcode IS approaching absolute-P after
# all (re-open the uniform claim) or (ii) the task selection was wrong.
# Both possibilities reframe the substrate's claim graph.
#
# Cost cap: $0.30 (lower than M3.43 because tasks are bounded-easy).

claim obs_frontier_does_not_dominate_on_single_step_formula_recall_regime_falsified: Bool @>=0.99 = False
claim frontier_dominates_voter_on_single_step_formula_recall_regime_bounded_q_half: Bool @>=0.78 = not obs_frontier_does_not_dominate_on_single_step_formula_recall_regime_falsified
falsified_when obs_frontier_does_not_dominate_on_single_step_formula_recall_regime_falsified

claim obs_m3_44_pre_registration_protocol_not_falsification_load_bearing: Bool @>=0.99 = False
claim m3_44_protocol_pre_registered_with_explicit_cost_latency_correctness_criteria: Bool @>=0.95 = not obs_m3_44_pre_registration_protocol_not_falsification_load_bearing
falsified_when obs_m3_44_pre_registration_protocol_not_falsification_load_bearing

claim obs_m3_44_will_exceed_30_cent_envelope_falsified: Bool @>=0.99 = False
claim m3_44_estimated_cost_at_or_below_30_cents_for_n_6_paired_formula_recall: Bool @>=0.85 = not obs_m3_44_will_exceed_30_cent_envelope_falsified
falsified_when obs_m3_44_will_exceed_30_cent_envelope_falsified

