# ============================================================
# SECTION OO - Path-to-goal at very-high-confidence (2026-05-03)
#
# Operator question: "do you have a confident plan to achieve our goal
# of (better and more intelligent general agent for human tasks) with
# very high confidence and how much that would cost"
#
# Goal restated precisely (per facts/16): "better and more intelligent
# than current frontier on the canonical 4-corner empirical envelope
# of human-task corpora — SWE-bench Verified (software), METR HCAST/
# RE-Bench (research), GAIA (general assistant), OSWorld (computer use)
# — at lower cost and competitive latency."
#
# Why this restatement is honest per atom 0015 + bcmea:
#   - "general agent for human tasks" is meaningful only against an
#     external referent corpus. The 4-corner envelope IS the canonical
#     external referent.
#   - Per bcmea, no agent can be absolutely best across ALL tasks
#     (frontier dominates contest math single-step formula recall per
#     SECTION NN bounded-Q evidence). The achievable goal is bounded-P
#     dominance within the practical-class envelope.
#
# CURRENT STATE per facts/19:
#   - Substrate primitives implemented + unit-tested ✓
#   - Working harness inherited (opencode fork) ✓
#   - Cost-dominance: sahih @0.88
#   - At-least-as-correct: sub-floor @0.80
#   - Much-more-intelligent: NOT YET (atom 0015 fired)
#   - Measurement-zero on 3 of 4 canonical corpora (B2/B3/B4)
#   - Partial measurement (B1 diagnose-only N=2) on 1 corpus
#
# GOAL IS ACHIEVABLE per facts/17:
#   Frontier-vs-human gap is 14-77pp across the 4-corner envelope.
#   Substantial headroom; goal is NOT saturated.
# GOAL APPROACH IS VALIDATED per facts/14 + facts/18:
#   Compound + orchestrator-subagent pattern is over-determined at
#   research mutawatir + production deployment (Anthropic 90.2% lift,
#   BAIR thesis, AlphaCode/Medprompt/Gemini-CoT).
# ============================================================

# ============================================================
# Phase decomposition for very-high-confidence goal achievement
# ============================================================

# PHASE I — measurement battery (anchors current substrate-vs-frontier
# delta across the 4-corner envelope). Without this, "better and more
# intelligent general agent for human tasks" is asserted-not-measured.
# Anti-fab guard fires unless we run ≥1 task per corpus.
#
# Cost per corpus (per M3.40 calibration $0.025/voter + $0.022/frontier
# per task, plus harness/scaffolding overhead):
#   - B1 SWE-bench Verified FULL loop, N=20 instances: $30-100
#     (full loop is more expensive than diagnose-only by ~10×; OpenAI's
#     reported per-task envelope ranges $1.50-5.00 for frontier agents
#     on SWE-bench Verified; cheapcode-witness expected to be similar
#     or less per cost-dominance).
#   - B2 METR HCAST slice, N=8 RE-Bench tasks: $5-15
#     (8-hour time horizon caps voter cost by wallclock).
#   - B3 GAIA Level-1 (easiest tier), N=20 questions: $3-8.
#   - B4 OSWorld light subset (browser-only), N=10 tasks: $5-15.
# Phase I total: $43-138. Honest mid-estimate $70-90.
claim obs_phase_i_measurement_battery_not_load_bearing_for_goal_falsified: Bool @>=0.99 = False
claim phase_i_4_corner_measurement_battery_anchors_current_substrate_vs_frontier_delta_at_70_dollars: Bool @>=0.92 = not obs_phase_i_measurement_battery_not_load_bearing_for_goal_falsified
falsified_when obs_phase_i_measurement_battery_not_load_bearing_for_goal_falsified

# PHASE II — substrate-harness integration engineering. Per facts/19 C1
# the harness is inherited but substrate primitives (atom 0007 anti-fab,
# atom 0010 cross-witness, atom 0015 transfer-overstated, conversion-
# factor estimator) are NOT YET wired into opencode's agent loop at
