# ============================================================
# Replacement Phase II-prime: design-space narrowing via facts/21
# ============================================================
#
# OLD Phase II: substrate-harness wiring with broad design space.
# Cost: $20-60 inference + 1-3 weeks engineering.
#
# NEW Phase II-prime: facts/21 disambiguation NARROWS the design space.
# Substrate-harness hooks must be PARALLEL-CONDORCET-SHAPE not
# SEQUENTIAL-COORDINATED-MAS. Hook contracts:
#   - NO inter-witness natural-language communication
#   - NO role specialization at the witness level
#   - synthesizer is the ONLY aggregation point per decision
#   - decision points fire only on UNCERTAINTY-DETECTED (otherwise
#     single-tier dispatch — voter overhead avoided when not needed)
# This narrowing reduces engineering risk substantially. 1-3 weeks
# becomes 1-2 weeks because the design contract is pre-specified.
