# SECTION BBB - M3.49 paired N=5 new shapes + honest cost-overfitting finding
# (2026-05-03, $0.036)
#
# Operator $1 budget — research-first per atom 0018. M3.49 spent $0.036
# on 5 NEW practical-class shape categories not tested in M3.47/48.
# Critical empirical finding: ROUTER COST-OVERFITTING on simple
# agentic-swe + closed-book shapes via Opus escalation. Honest atom
# 0013 disclosure preserved.
#
# RESULTS (full receipt at runs/m3-49-paired-new-shapes/summary.json):
#
# | Task | Shape | Auto target | Cost ratio | Notes |
# |------|-------|-------------|------------|-------|
# | T6 agentic-swe | agentic-swe | claude-opus-4 | **22.12×** | Opus 22× MORE expensive on simple bug fix |
# | T7 classification | classification | llama-4-scout | 0.004× | 250× cheaper (massive win) |
# | T8 closed-book | closed-book | claude-opus-4 | **5.123×** | Opus 5× MORE expensive on year recall |
# | T9 real-world-coding | multistep-general | gpt-5-mini | 0.177× | ~6× cheaper |
# | T10 multi-step | multistep-general | gpt-5-mini | 0.087× | ~12× cheaper |
# | M3.49 AGGREGATE | — | — | **1.839×** | MORE expensive on this N=5! |
# | CUMULATIVE (M3.47+48+49 N=15) | — | — | **0.250× (4× cheaper)** | aggregate dominance HOLDS |
#
# CRITICAL HONEST FINDING — UNIFORM COST DOMINANCE FALSIFIED:
#
# The "cheapcode-auto uniformly cheaper than gpt-5.5" claim is now
# EMPIRICALLY FALSIFIED. Counter-examples:
#   - T1 bounded-code (haiku): 1.5× more expensive on simple one-liner
#   - T6 agentic-swe (opus-4): 22× more expensive on simple bug fix
#   - T8 closed-book (opus-4): 5× more expensive on year recall
#   - T5 hard-reasoning voter: 7× SLOWER (latency, not cost)
#
# ROOT CAUSE: facts/09 routing rules optimize per-shape for MAX-quality
# benchmark performance (Opus MCP-Atlas 77.3% on agentic-swe), not for
# COST-PER-SIMPLE-TASK. For simple instances of agentic-swe, closed-book,
# or bounded-code, the routed specialist is OVERKILL — gpt-5.5 alone is
# already at p>=0.99 and cheap.
#
# WHERE CHEAPCODE-AUTO STILL WINS DECISIVELY (5/8 shape categories):
#   - math-chain → deepseek-flash: 75× cheaper on simple math
#   - classification → llama-4-scout: 250× cheaper on simple sentiment
#   - phd-factual → gemini-2.5-flash: 3× cheaper on physics explanation
#   - multistep-general → gpt-5-mini: 6-15× cheaper on planning + multistep
#   - long-context → grok-4-fast: documented 3pt accuracy edge at 1M tokens
#
# WHERE CHEAPCODE-AUTO LOSES vs naive gpt-5.5 baseline (3/8 shape categories):
#   - bounded-code-simple (haiku-4.5): 1.5× more expensive
#   - agentic-swe-simple (claude-opus-4): 22× more expensive
#   - closed-book-simple (claude-opus-4): 5× more expensive
#
# Bounded-form goal CLAIM SHARPENED (atom 0013 + atom 0015 honest):
# cheapcode-auto is cheaper than naive gpt-5.5 on AGGREGATE across
# diverse practical tasks (~4× cheaper at N=15) BUT NOT uniformly per
# shape. The savings are CONCENTRATED in 5/8 shape categories;
# cost-LOSSES on 3/8 shape categories where Opus over-routing fires.
#
# Future v2.x router refinement (deferred per atom 0011 cost-discipline):
# add per-shape COMPLEXITY-DETECTION sub-classifier so Opus only fires
# for genuinely-agentic SWE tasks (multi-file, tool-using), not for
# one-line bug fixes.
# ============================================================

# Empirical finding — uniform cost dominance falsified
claim obs_uniform_cost_dominance_per_shape_holds_falsified: Bool @>=0.99 = True
claim uniform_cost_dominance_per_shape_holds_across_8_practical_categories: Bool @>=0.10 = not obs_uniform_cost_dominance_per_shape_holds_falsified
